title.narrative: Tanzania Productive Social Safety Net Project II

description.narrative: The objective of the Productive Social Safety Net II Project in Tanzania is to improve access to income-earning opportunities and socio-economic services for targeted poor households while enhancing and protecting the human capital of their children. This project is comprised of two components. The first component will provide beneficiary households with an integrated package of support, including a foundational package and livelihoods support. The two subcomponents are: (1) Cash Transfers; (2) Public Works. The second subcomponent is Strengthening Institutional Capacity and Integrated Delivery Systems. The two subcomponents are: (1) Institutional Capacity Enhancement, and; (2) Integrated delivery system development.

condition.narrative: The Recipient shall ensure that no activity under the Project shall involve irrigation schemes or related schemes in or linked tointernational waterways or important tributaries of such international waterways (Schedule 2, Section I A of Financing Agreement).

The Recipient shall not later than ninety (90) days after the Effective Date submit, in form and substance satisfactory to theAssociation, terms of reference for the external audit for the Project (Schedule 2, Section IV 1 of Financing Agreement)
